Elements of programming interviews

# 

<span key="7793c24be5014538b437956f192b3f86"><span offset-key="7793c24be5014538b437956f192b3f86:0">Chapter 1 - strategies for a great interview</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="8de32c15a90e43b68a81f3053e17cff1"><span offset-key="8de32c15a90e43b68a81f3053e17cff1:0">Once you have an algorithm, it is important to present it in a clear manner. Your solution will be much simpler if you take advantage of libraries such as Java Collections or C++ Boost.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="93b9664c2ae54ec3924e9d3600db8240"><span offset-key="93b9664c2ae54ec3924e9d3600db8240:0">Important that you use the language you are most comfortable with.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="6b86067d0f994196a2328df08bbb3097"><span offset-key="6b86067d0f994196a2328df08bbb3097:0">Master the libraries, especially the data structures.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="56e0330f337b4c80b78024bd1175b60a"><span offset-key="56e0330f337b4c80b78024bd1175b60a:0">Do not waste time and lose credibility trying to remember how to pass an explicit comparator to a BST constructor.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="1a4086876ae44c729fd818da6e003913"><span offset-key="1a4086876ae44c729fd818da6e003913:0">Remember that a hash function should use exactly those fields which are used in the equality check. A comparison function should be transitive.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="ae69c46833b14d6ea2093b6d72834c38"><span offset-key="ae69c46833b14d6ea2093b6d72834c38:0">Focus on the top-level algorithm:</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="5f252cc69d10420f961e93051ab9cd5f"><span offset-key="5f252cc69d10420f961e93051ab9cd5f:0">It's OK to use functions that you will implement later. This will let you focus on the main part of the algorithm, will penalize you less if you don't complete the algorithm. (Hash, equals, and compare functions are good candidates for deferred implementation.) Specify that you will handle main algorithm first, then comer cases. Add TODO comments for portions that you want to come back to.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="699be98acd654d66adac081f0939653f"><span offset-key="699be98acd654d66adac081f0939653f:0">Manage the whiteboard:</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="a88230c437be427c9b4b7d81b3ab8663"><span offset-key="a88230c437be427c9b4b7d81b3ab8663:0">You will likely use more of the board than you expect, so start at the top-left comer.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="11aeb75aa544449da378fdc686dc3a2e"><span offset-key="11aeb75aa544449da378fdc686dc3a2e:0">Make use of functions skip implementing anything that's trivial (e.g., finding the maximum of an array) or standard (e.g., a thread pool).</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="a18cd1f688a4412b952a0f79a59924f1"><span offset-key="a18cd1f688a4412b952a0f79a59924f1:0">Have a convention for identifiers, e.g., i , j , k for array indices, A , B , C for arrays, u , v , w for vectors, s for a String, sb for a StringBuilder, etc.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="cdb9d7b5f5a7457d80c62a2f9adcabae"><span offset-key="cdb9d7b5f5a7457d80c62a2f9adcabae:0">Assume valid inputs.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="f65c1cf2f55b4eed9f05b7bf717b31af"><span offset-key="f65c1cf2f55b4eed9f05b7bf717b31af:0">Test for comer cases.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="4829a6bb625f4d578e1d689957eb0ba0"><span offset-key="4829a6bb625f4d578e1d689957eb0ba0:0">For many problems, your general idea may work for most valid inputs but there may be pathological valid inputs where your algorithm (or your implementation of it) fails.</span></span>

        -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

            <span key="dd553ab0b6824eca994ffa7cd95da813"><span offset-key="dd553ab0b6824eca994ffa7cd95da813:0">For example, your binary search code may crash if the input is an empty array; or you may do arithmetic without considering the possibility of overflow.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="6c015b83817b427c92c64d11af5912cd"><span offset-key="6c015b83817b427c92c64d11af5912cd:0">It is important to systematically consider these possibilities. If there is time, write unit tests.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="10a65279e65d40b19abd18a15210c341"><span offset-key="10a65279e65d40b19abd18a15210c341:0">Small, extreme, or random inputs make for good stimuli. Don't forget to add code for checking the result. Occasionally, the code to handle obscure corner cases may be too complicated to implement in an interview setting. If so, you should mention to the interviewer that you are aware of these problems, and could address them if required.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="7d96da907b9f47eaaebd2e1da6bef21f"><span offset-key="7d96da907b9f47eaaebd2e1da6bef21f:0">Syntax</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="e51234f6c5a64f3baa5154bf98cb7a91"><span offset-key="e51234f6c5a64f3baa5154bf98cb7a91:0">Interviewers rarely penalize you for small syntax errors since modern IDE excel at handling these details.</span></span>

        -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

            <span key="f7777e718c704ebd944586f166399670"><span offset-key="f7777e718c704ebd944586f166399670:0">However, lots of bad syntax may result in the impression that you have limited coding experience. Once you are done writing your program, make a pass through it to fix any obvious syntax errors before claiming you are done.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="612f4f7ce13042df99676c9ea5e31ab0"><span offset-key="612f4f7ce13042df99676c9ea5e31ab0:0">Know your interviewers & the company.</span></span>

    <span key="1c55e9fe89224ea0952527cb6496b203"><span offset-key="1c55e9fe89224ea0952527cb6496b203:0">-</span></span>
